# Pull Secret Required

This file is a placeholder. The oc-mirror container expects a pull secret at `/workspace/pull-secret.txt`.

## How to get your pull secret:

1. Visit: https://console.redhat.com/openshift/install/pull-secret
2. Download your pull secret JSON file

## Usage:

### For Podman/Docker:
```bash
# Mount the pull secret file directly
podman run --rm \
  -v /path/to/pull-secret.json:/workspace/pull-secret.txt:ro \
  -v oc-mirror-data:/workspace/content \
  oc-mirror-autoshift:latest workflow-to-disk
```

### For Kubernetes/Pipeline:
```bash
# Create Kubernetes secret (one-time setup)
oc create secret generic oc-mirror-pull-secret \
  --from-file=.dockerconfigjson=/path/to/pull-secret.json \
  --type=kubernetes.io/dockerconfigjson \
  --namespace=openshift-pipelines

# Pipeline automatically mounts this secret at /workspace/pull-secret.txt
```

### Alternative - Use existing cluster pull secret:
```bash
oc get secret pull-secret -n openshift-config -o jsonpath='{.data.\.dockerconfigjson}' | \
  base64 -d > /tmp/pull-secret.json

oc create secret generic oc-mirror-pull-secret \
  --from-file=.dockerconfigjson=/tmp/pull-secret.json \
  --type=kubernetes.io/dockerconfigjson \
  --namespace=openshift-pipelines

rm -f /tmp/pull-secret.json
```

⚠️  DO NOT commit actual pull secrets to git!